'''Differential Mobility Detector (DMD)''' is a type of microelectromechanical system, radio frequency modulated [[Ion mobility spectrometry|IMS]] (MEMS RF-IMS) device. [[Image:CP-4900 4chan with DMD.jpg|thumb|right|Varian CP-4900 MicroGC, four channel, with Differential Mobility Detector (first from the right)]]
Though its small in size, it easily fits into portable units, such as transferable gas chromatographs or drug/explosives sensors. For instance, it was incorporated by [[Varian]] in its CP-4900 DMD MicroGC, and by [[Thermo Fisher Scientific|Thermo Fisher]] in its EGIS Defender system, designed to detect narcotics and explosives in transportation or other homeland security applications.
== Specifications for DMD as part of Varian CP-4900 MicroGC<ref>Varian document CP501677, February 2004.</ref> ==
* Detection limit: 100 ppb for MES * Dynamic range: 10<sup>3</sup> * [[Relative standard deviation|RSD]] < 2% at 10 times the [[Low detection limit|LDL]] * Gas requirements: 400 mL/min ‘Zero’ Air or N<sub>2</sub>.<ref>The authors of [http://gazanaliz.ru/articles/DMD/DMD.htm this article] note that one 5 liter gas cylinder of [http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/zero_air Zero Air] was enough for three to four days of normal work in the field.</ref>
However, independent researchers<ref>[http://gazanaliz.ru/articles/DMD/DMD.htm ''in Russian'': Zhiltsov I.N. and Chupin V.V., '''New Possibilities of Gas Chromatographic Analysis: the Differential Mobility Detector (DMD)''']</ref> report that [[Relative standard deviation|RSD]] for such compounds as [[hydrogen sulfide]], [[Methanethiol|methyl mercaptan]], and [[Ethanethiol|ethyl mercaptan]] is from 4 to 11%.
